1)
Strategies:
Whatever - put mark in a random valid position.
Clever - put marks by order from (0,0) position to (lastPosition, lastPosition).
Genius - put marks by order from (lastPosition, lastPosition) position to (0,0) against clever,
         if the clever is about to win the Genius block him.
         against the random the Genius play like the Clever.
2)
a. The benefits of the players classes that implement the same interface is:
we can create a several players that act the same (at that case - put mark in the board),
but with difference strategy.
b. The Pillars that this project design is represent are: Polymorphism and Encapsulation.